content.description: techy goodness all the way.  good for a beginner leader although theres some sections where you could possibly get the willies!
content.location: starts off on a one bolt slightly slightly steep couple of moves to a ledge then up through another slightly steep bolt to the slabish vertical face to anchors. located on the right side of Cody Night Rodeo Wall

content.description: A thin start leads to fun climbing on cool holds for the first 5 bolts, then to a horizontal break beneath a short bulge. Get a good rest, then fire straight over the bulge past the final bolt(crux) and run it out to the anchor!
content.location:
Located to the right of 'Cowgirls Smuggling YO-YOs'

Of the 4 routes on this side of the wall, it is the 3rd route from the left.

content.description:
Formerly "Cowgirls Smuggling Yoyos" and changed by CK.

Black streak up the Nite Rodeo Wall, crux up high. Entire route is quite sharp and dirty.

Climb a short slab to gain vertical terrain for a few clips, and reach a horizontal break below the bulge. Rest here, then fire the crux bulge past one last bolt before a run out section to the anchor. A bit sharp?

fun fun climbing up to a couple little cruxes.  little dirty but nothing to worry about (no rocks falling off or anything just a little dusty).  sharpish holds that are great for footwork (not your shoes) and not so great for your finger tips but if this is in your level its a good climb and you should get on it.
content.location: just left of Sensory System and pretty much the exact description for the start!
